content.description: Climb the slab right of Bart to a crack, then follow this to the top.
content.protection: Trad, Trees at top for anchor.

content.description: Like most of the routes on the main slab, this is a good beginner route.   Climb the crack past the jog and up to the top. It's a bit bushy in the very wide part of the crack as you near the end, but it is also quite easy.
content.protection: Double 3 - 4" cams plus medium cams   There are trees at the top, some with rope anchors.
content.location: This route lies near the right side of the main slab, starting at a small left-facing corner with a wide crack, that has a slight jog left about 20' up.

content.description: Small, low-angle slab (50 to 75' tall) up and left of Lower-Low Slab; left of and below the bulk of Upper Slab. It is right of the Green Stamp Walls. Several crack lines run up this slab.   The routes on this slab are all beginner routes; most are on the extreme low end of fifth class climbing.
